              <div class="question">
                  <h3>What are some of the unique features of Deaf culture?</h3>
                  <br><br>
                  <h4>Values, behaviors, and traditions of Deaf culture include the following:</h4>
                  <ul>
                      <li>
                          <p>A reliance on eyesight, including the use of a visual language, which then influences the
                            configuration of an environment. In support of a visual lifestyle, architectural and interior designs
                            highlight lighting, both adequate and creative; open floor plans; and spatial positioning of
                            furniture that enhance visual sight lines</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                          <p>Valuing the sign language of the region and supporting sign language use in educational settings,
                            such as bilingual ASL/English programs in the United States</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                          <p> A high degree of networking and deep connections within the Deaf community</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                          <p> Maintaining cultural traditions through social activities
                            including athletic events, Deaf clubs, organizational
                            involvement, and school reunions</p>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                          <p>Promoting Deaf culture through art forms such as painting, drawing, film, folklore, literature,
                            storytelling, and poetry
                          </p>
                      </li>
                  </ul>
              </div>
